column5: Oh yeah, GATOR CITY!!
awesome!!
Wow...some really nice Pike there Dave!!...I'm jealous too!

Wow!!! What a day!!! Awesome warm temps and light tropical breezes and super fast action!!!! I left the house at first light and was set up and fishing about an hour later. Before I could get my jigging line set up I had my first hit on my tip up. After resetting I headed into the hut to continue with my jig stick, I didn't get to far, FLAG!!! I ran back to my tip up second fish. As I was dropping my bait back down I hit another, and another......... It was 45 minutes from the time I dropped my first line before I managed to get my second line in the water. After 3 hours I had iced 20 pike and lossed/missed a bunch more!!! I ended up with about 1/2 dozen over 30" with one over 40". I was fishing solo again today and man that was a lot of work!!! I think I need a rum now.  Here's a few pics of the better ones.
Very nice lookin Northerns Dave, and girthy as well, enjoy the tropical weather while you can
Awesome!!
Tell me your arms aren't sore!   That's like having a good day of Perch fishing down here!  Rob C
Sounds like a perfect day!
Wow, great stuff Dave
Nice peice a fish'en Dave , way better then i did .......
Now THAT is a good days work!
Your hands must be shredded. Great report and pics

That's insane.  Getting just one fish like that would be a good day for most guys.  A couple like that in a day might be my best day all season.  That's a heckava resource you've got up there...but it seems like you know what you're doing too.  Thanks for the report.
Awesome Dave!!!! Since we're practically neighbors I should head up that way!!  Gotta love the early ice we both get.
Sounds like a lot of fun buddy and a perfect cardio workout to boot.  Now let's see some big lakers!
Man, I would love to fish NWT!  That's awesome.
Another great report Dave. You're going to have to start blurring the backgrounds eh?
Awesome fishin Dave !!! Keep em comin'
That's next on the list Mike.    Yeah Roy, I wouldn't want all you Southerners invading my fishin' spots would I.
Actually he did Roy, he was really fishing out in front of the CN Tower.  Nice work Dave that sounds like a day of fishing any of us "Southeners" would love to have!
Yep, I was fishin' Toronto Island can't you tell?
Nice fish pix, thanx.  If I left Wednesday morning (Sudbury) would I be In Yellowknife by noon Saturday?? LOL
awesome winter pike dave !!!
I love these reports man....keep'em coming!  Are you waiting for safe ice for lakers, or for the season to open?  Cuz I'd like to see summa those too, please

Neither. Wanted to get the pike fishing done and am waiting for the days to get a little longer as it's a further hike to the laker spots. There are no seasons here to speak of. The road system laker spots are C&R in September and October and a 1 fish limit the rest of the year. All other spots are open year round with different retention limits for Great Slave compared to the rest of the Territory.
amature...you gotta know when you drill your jigging hole closer to your tip up hole.  NICE fish..
Well done Dave, some real beauts there for sure !!!!
Fantastic Fish, Jealous
